title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1993-09-21
description: Hell In A Bucket, Bertha, The Same Thing, Peggy-O, Broken Arrow, Tennessee Jed, The Music Never Stopped Here Comes Sunshine, Way to Go Home, Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Jam-> Drums-> Space-> The Last Time-> Stella Blue-> Sugar Magnolia, E: The Weight

reviews.review_text: Good Show A+++++ Quality, Show, and Setlist.  Great show.

Show askew Good attempt at being lucid.  Listen to Garcia's playing on Sunshine and his singing on Terrapin.  Phil's playing is really good throughout.  Nice last day of summer in NYC.  Harmonizing is actually satisfactory on this show.  Not much of a show after drums and space.  What happened backstage?

9-21-93 Decent show. High quality dsbd remastered by C miller. I'm not a huge fan of the post Brent era although I went to a couple of shows in '91 that were real humdingers. I think I would have liked them better if they had went back to their roots and just stuck with Hornsby on piano without Vince. I'm not a Vince hatter though.
